items.name: Emilia Mernes [LORA]
items.description:
V1.0

  1. Spanish:

Las imágenes han sigo generadas con el modelo realista EpicRealism.

Es posible que el nombre del LORA cambie, así que no lo copies directamente de CIVITAI, mejor selecciónalo del apartado de LORAS de Stable Diffusion para que no haya errores en la generación de imágenes.

Mi configuración usando EpicRealism:

  • Lora Strength: 1

  • Prompt: Explicación simple de la imagen (pruebe primero sin palabras clave adicionales)

    En el caso de esta Lora, el prompt debe comenzar con "A woman...".

  • Prompt negativo: cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2), asian, chinese, (epiCNegative:0.9)

  • Sampling steps: >20 (si la imagen tiene errores o artefactos, use steps más altos)

  • CFG Scale: 5

  • Sampling method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Tamaño: 512x768 o 768x512

  • Hires fix: 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G (Denoising strenght: 0.35, Upscale by: 2)

  1. English:

The images have been generated with the realistic model EpicRealism.

It is possible that the name of the LORA will change, so do not copy it directly from CIVITAI, rather select it from the LORAS section of Stable Diffusion so that there are no errors in the generation of images.

My setup using EpicRealism:

  • Lora Strength: 1

  • Prompt: simple explanation of the image (try first without extra keywords)

    In the case of this LORA, the prompt must begin with "A woman...".

  • Negative prompt: cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2), asian, chinese, (epiCNegative:0.9)

  • Sampling steps: >20 (if image has errors or artefacts use higher Steps)

  • CFG Scale: 5

  • Sampling method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Size: 512x768 or 768x512

  • Hires fix: 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G (Denoising strength: 0.35, Upscale by: 2)

items.name: Rory (Ceehaz) | Dog Knight RPG | LoCon
items.description:
Rory, a Doberman scout, from the webcomic by Ceehaz "Dog knight RPG". Works best on 1.0. Training done on NAI.

This one is a LoCon which can be placed in LoRA folder on Automatic1111 1.5.1 so make sure to update otherwise place in Lycoris folder.

Trigger: "RoryCeehaz, furry" always needed, for consistency add "orange eyes, muscular, expressionless" to her proper look.

Suggestions:

  • As this is a furry character not all models/checkpoints will be able to make her so test out several for best results.

  • "RoryArmor" for her armor outfit, I found adding "green, gloves, black gloves, shoulder armor, breastplate" can help but the outfit is a bit weak due to low data.

  • If the eyes are weak add "Orange eyes".

  • "tail" can get the tail to show but its random cause SD does not like tails.

  • If you remove "furry" she will become more humanoid which can look pretty nice.

Buff doggo what more can one ask for, this one was a another fun test to improve at training custom skin colors. I think it turned out really well so I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.name: Jean-Michel Basquiat SDXL 1.0 art style lora
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Jean-Michel Basquiat art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Jean-Michel Basquiat is a neo-expressionist and primitivist artist and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 resolution and is able to produce higher details than if you were to simply put his name into your prompt. You can however add "in the style of Jean-Michel Basquiat" to your prompt along with the LoRa and trigger for a slightly different effect.

I use this at a weight of around 1 but you may have to go higher sometimes depending on the prompt. If your prompt starts to lose its "Basquiatness" you can bump the weight up incrementally as high as 1.7. I used clip skip 1 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. CFG 15 is nice and crisp and I think works best for this art style but feel free to experiment.

The main trigger is b4sq and there are no additional tags for this art style. Be creative with your txt2img or use img2img to guide the basic composition and colors.

Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

items.name: BlackRealStockings – Lace top black stockings
items.description:
The model is trained using a dedicated dataset, focusing on black stockings with lace tops. The first aim was to improve the rendering of black stockings for the Realistic Vision models, where stockings show often problems with lace top appearance.

_____________________________________________________________________________

IMPORTANT: The serie RealStockings is made by 3 different Loras:

-          BlackRealStockings, this Lora;

-          WhiteRealStockings, specific for white lace top stockings, downloadable at:

https://civitai.com/models/118574/whiterealstockings-lace-top-white-stockings

-          TanRealStockings, specific for tan lace top stockings, downloadable at:

https://civitai.com/models/111186/tanrealstockings-lace-top-sheer-stockings

All three Loras can be used together in the same image and make a sort of bundle, providing the same outfit for stockings of different colors.

 _____________________________________________________________________________

BlackRealStockings is based on SD 1.5, is optimized for Realistic Vision (checked also with 5.0) but also gives good results with other models, by changing the weight of the model or the weight of the trigger word.

Trigger word:

BlackRealStockings

To ensure that lace top bands are visible add in the prompt:

visibile BlackRealStockings top lace bands

 

To avoid the rendering of garter belt or suspenders write in the negative prompt:

(suspenders:1.3), (garter belt:1.3),

Sampling steps recommended: 25-50

 

CFG Scale: 7

Sampler Suggested:

DPM ++ 2M SDE KARRAS for Realistic Vision

Euler a for non realistic models.

CHECKPOINTS TESTED

Model and trigger word weight

REALISTIC VISION V2.0, V3.0, V4.0 and V5.0

weight model suggested: 1

trigger word weight: 1-1.1

If prompt is very long and structured, inpainting is suggested to obtain a more effective result, especially on lace top bands.

Effectiveness on more checkpoints will be tested.

On Realistic vision this Lora is compatible with Opentoe heels/sandals with legwears. The use of Opentoe lora is reccomended with inpainting algorithm.

items.name: FluffyMix
items.description:
V4 is out!

This version uses the same models as V3 (with updated epoch versions) while adding a new base, Deliberate V2! Deliberate and 526Mix are combined with 67% 526Mix and 33% Deliberate average weight merge, and then used just like 526Mix was used in previous versions. Additionally, this mix used block weight merging in Comfy to merge together the e6-laion + Polyfur part with the FluffyRock NoPE part at 0.5 CLIP merge, and the result is train differenced onto P.A.W.F.E.C.T just like V3. One last thing, the name is now officially changed to FluffyMix to make it easier to remember.

V3 is out!

This version uses fluffyrock-NoPE-e144-terminal-snr-vpred-e63.safetensors, e6-laion-576-704-832-lion-e81-terminal-snr-vpred-e30.safetensors, polyfur-lion-e87-terminal-snr-vpred-e36.safetensors, pawfect-alpha-e48-None.safetensors, and v1.5 of 526Mix. e6-laion operates similarly to Polyfur and includes the same MiniGPT4 captioned photographs, but e6-laion is also trained on anime style images from booru sites. e6-laion and Polyfur are merged together at a 0.5 weight average merge for the purposes of this mix. FluffyRock NoPE also operates similarly to FluffyRock Vpred, and while both models use the same dataset and are both v-prediction, FluffyRock NoPE messes with the text interpretation part of its model in order to remove positional encoding, meaning it doesn't require a token limit. It isn't known if this is passed on through merging, however NoPE did have a different and more preferable aesthetic from its sibling, which is why it was chosen. Finally, P.A.W.F.E.C.T is another v-prediction model trained on images from FurAffinity. The unique aspects of this model are its aesthetic and tags, as FurAffinity tags are often diverse and sparse, meaning images are often incompletely tagged and sometimes use uncommon tags. This means P.A.W.F.E.C.T both provides unique tagging and a unique aesthetic to this mix.

V2 is out!

This version uses polyfur-lion-e76-terminal-snr-vpred-e25.safetensors and fluffyrock-576-704-832-960-1088-lion-low-lr-e126-terminal-snr-vpred-e99 mixed with 526Mix to provide the model with even better knowledge and aesthetics. Polyfur is special, as it attempts to include both high quality photographs autocaptioned by MiniGPT4 in its dataset alongside furry images, so that you get the best of both worlds. The model is early in its lifespan, but contains enough specialised knowledge that it significantly improves the quality of this mix.

Unofficial merge of fluffyrock-576-704-832-960-1088-lion-low-lr-e126-terminal-snr-vpred-e99 and https://civitai.com/models/15022/526mix-v14 using train difference with the supermerger extension in automatic1111.

Train difference is explained here https://github.com/hako-mikan/sd-webui-supermerger/blob/main/calcmode_en.md#train, and is what allows this model to exist. TLDR, this model uses the a1111 supermerger extension to merge 526Mix with FluffyRock vpred using these settings: 526Mix is set as model A, fluffyrock vpred as model B, v1-5-pruned (sd base model) as model C, add difference as the merge mode, train difference as the calculation mode, alpha is set to 1, and the output is saved as fp16 safetensors.

This model requires a config and CFG Rescale. Download the config file and put it next to the regular model in your stable diffusion models folder. If you use a1111, install the CFG Rescale extension here: https://github.com/Seshelle/CFG_Rescale_webui. If you use comfy, download the sampler_rescalecfg file from here https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI_experiments and put it in your custom nodes folder. Recommended settings are 7.5 for CFG and 0.7 for CFG Rescale.

Credit goes to zatochu on the furry diffusion discord for figuring this out, and credit to 526christian for creating the 526mix and lodestone for creating fluffyrock.

items.name: General Purpose Typography Style
items.description:
Intention

This LoRA was created to aid in the creation of letterforms / characters using the img2img process. The starting point was the question whether it is possible to create clean, typographic charaters using Stable Diffusion. The main focus of this LoRA is the creation of decorative / display fonts.

It is trained on a custom dataset on high contrast typographic imagery with flexibility in mind.

Base model for the training was v1-5-pruned.safetensors.

Use

This model is intended to be used in the img2img process. Generic letterforms (ideally white on black background) are used as an input. Playing with a noise fill for the letters or a blur can lead to interesting results, too.

To use the LoRA just include the following tokens in the construction of your prompt:

zhuj, typography

A starting point for experimentation with reasonable flexibility:

zhuj, typography, black background, monochrome, (((style description))) <lora:zhuj_typography:1.5>

Further refinement can be achieved using the Negative Prompt.

CFG scale of around 10.5 and denoising between .7 and .9 are a good. starting point.

items.name: Serperior (Fluffyrock-LoRa)

The grass snake! 2nd LoRa of the LoRamon series I'm doing, trained with fluffyrock and 100 images

I'd also use weights of 0.7-1

I suggest using Clip Skip 1, not 2, cause it screws with a lot of stuff with the images.

Some issues you should be aware of:

This model can do feral, but not very well due to the limited dataset I had.

If you find any other issues with it, let me know! it helps out a ton with me updating it too!

(AMEDS RAMBLING SECTION)

This model took me a lot of days, changing models for it to train with, and manual tag editing

LoRa making isn't easy, and this model isn't the best.

I'm updating this one soon, has too many issues and I feel like I could've done better (mainly because I now know a lot more stuff)

Anyway, if you read this far, congrats. Thanks for listening to my rambles and struggles n shit, hopefully, you enjoy the model at its current version.

items.name: UnsafeXL
items.description:
This is probably best described as designed to generate epic images of sexy women in sexy outfits. I basically just kept adding sets of images with tags for concepts that I wanted to generate for, then doing a block merge optimized for aesthetic score using the Bayesian optimizer extension. DreamshaperXL alpha also was merged in the same way early on, so some of that is in there.

The data sets I used were tagged using Danbooru tags, so that is the tagging style I used with the generated images, but CLIP-style tagging should still work.

Concepts trained on: action, broken armor, cracked skin, glowing veins, cyberpunk, dual wielding + handguns, dynamic pose, fighting stance, holding weapon, monster girl, sniper rifle, steampunk, topless, torn clothes, torn wings.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: Trained separate models on top of animagineXL and VenusXL, then merged those together and then with UnsafeXL 1.0, then further trained on top of that. The dataset of around 3.5k images now contains some photorealistic images, as well as things such as underwater scenes, "horror \(theme\)", and individual pieces of armor (such as pauldrons, rerebraces, vambraces, faulds, etc.). All images are also tagged better with "anime" or "photorealistic", so it should be easier to prompt for the those types of styles. I also tried a new thing where I trained on images for the first 200 noising steps (similar to how the SDXL refiner works) that were low quality or had bad anatomy, but merged it at negative weight.

items.name: Psy Animated XL
items.description:
This is my own rendition of my favorite SD 1.5 model ported to SDXL. This model was trained on 5000 images generated using a custom LoRa combined with ReV Animated! Credit goes to s6yx for his creation of Rev Animated

Please consider a donation to my Ko-fi or a 5 star review

Model Review:

  • Style: This model has the ability to create a variety of styles but focuses on 2.5D like images.

  • Kind of generations:

    • Fantasy

    • Sci-fi

    • Anime

    • semi-realistic

    • Painted

    • Landscapes

    • Psychedelic

    • High Details

    • Artistic

  • It works best on these resolution dimensions:

    • 1024x1024

    • 768x1344

    • 1024x1536

    • 768x1024

  • Problem areas

    • This model has some difficulty with hands when describing complex prompts

    • It wasn't trained on any realistic images, so I cannot confirm if it has that capacity.

    • Not trained on any NSFW work

Prompting:

  • Steps 30-40 seem to work good

  • CFG of 4-10 was experimented with, it tends to work better at CFG 6-9

  • Hires fix works well for some images, try putting the denoise at 0.55 and upscale at 1.4

Please experiment with your prompting, this was trained using no captions so you will find that sometimes prompting can cause mutations to occur in the images, This is generally the price we pay for having incredible composition and stylization in our models. There is so much you can create in this model, I believe it maintains the versatility that SDXL 1.0 has while allowing for greater color scheme, details, and composition while lending toward a semi-realistic 2.5D style.

Disclaimer:

Do not sell this model on any website without permissions from creator (me)

Credit me if you use my model in your own merges

I do not authorize this model to be used on generative services

items.description:
鋼鉄の神話は進化する。

The myth of steel evolves.

概要

アニメに出てきそうなロボットやメカを生成するLoraです。ヒロイックなデザインのスーパーロボットから、スタイリッシュなリアルロボ、地に足のついたミリタリーロボットまで、様々なデザインの描き分けに対応しております。

SD1.5版の「Super robot diffusion」よりも更に表現力やディテールが向上しており、フォトリアルな絵やイラスト調の絵の出力に対応しております。

なお、このLoraは特定の機種を出すためのものではございません。あくまでそれっぽいデザインのロボットを出すものです。

about

This Lora is for generating robot and mecha of various genres that might appear in an anime.

It supports a wide range of designs, from heroic to military.

It has even more expression and detail than the SD 1.5 version 'Super robot diffusion', and supports the output of photo-realistic and illustration-style pictures.

In addition, this Lora is not intended to output any particular well-known robot.

推奨設定

チェックポイント: counterfeit xl

サンプラー:DPM++ SDE Karras (Personal preference)

CFG Scale: 7

Lora強度: 0.6～0.8

Recommended Setting

Checkpoint: counterfeit xl

Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Personal preference)

CFG Scale: 7

Lora Weight: 0.6～0.8

スタイル説明

6つのスタイルの描き分けが可能となっており、プロンプトにトリガーワードを入れることによってスタイルを適用することが可能です。

Style Description

By entering trigger words specifying various styles, it is possible to draw different designs for different genres.

・スーパーロボットスタイル Super Robot Style (SRS)

みんな大好きスーパーロボット。ヒロイックな装飾が盛り込まれており、ゴテゴテな飾りがついているロボットスタイルです。

とにかく理屈抜きでカッコいいロボットが欲しい方はこちらを使用してください。

This is a robot genre with mainly fancy decorations and heroic designs.

They are decorated with crystals on their chests, horns on their heads, etc.

I just want a robot with a cool design! Use this one if you want a robot with a cool design.

サンプルプロンプト

sample prompt

(SRS), (a ((super robot)) with sleek and menacing design:1.2), (large head:1.8),(full armor:1.5), (full body),(heroick parts), glowing eyes, full body, highly detailed, <lora:srdxl_v1f:0.8>

・ミリタリーロボットスタイル Military Robot Style (MRS)

地に足のついた軍事的なロボットが欲しい？大丈夫です。

皆さんがむせそうな泥臭い武骨なロボットも出すことも可能です。

Unlike Super Robot, this robot genre has no fancy decorations and has a military weapon-like, martial and massive design.

Use this if you want a muddy, down-to-earth robot.

サンプルプロンプト

sample prompt

(MRS) ,super fine concept art, extremely detailed, a heavy mech, hard surface, hawken, sci-fi, battlefield, <lora:srdxl_v1f:0.8>

・リアルロボットスタイル Real Robot Style (RRS)

いわゆる某有名な機動なんちゃらっぽいロボットが描けるスタイルです。ミリタリーロボットは武骨過ぎるし、スーパーロボットは飾り過ぎるからちょうどいい中間のスタイルが欲しい方にうってつけです。

スタイリッシュでかつ程よいミリタリー感とヒロイック感が融合しているスタイルです。

This robot genre falls between super-robot and real-robot.

They are mainly stylishly designed and have a slight military component.

サンプルプロンプト

sample prompt

(RRS), a (((mecha))) with sleek and menacing design, glowing eyes, full body, highly detailed, <lora:srdxl_v1f:0.8>

・ファンタジーロボットスタイル Fantasy Robot Style (FRS)

まるで異世界に登場しそうな甲冑をまとったロボットスタイルです。武骨なメカニックパーツと優雅なゴシックパーツが融合したスタイルとなっています。

メカニック要素とゴシック要素がアンバランスなこともありますので、適度にパーツに関するプロンプトを入れると良い結果が出せるでしょう。

This robot genre has an armoured form and armour, and is decorated in a gothic style.

The designs are similar to those of super robots, but are reminiscent of warriors such as knights and samurai.

It is more difficult to adjust the design to both mechanical and armoured elements, so it can work well if you supplement the parts and elements with prompts.

サンプルプロンプト

sample prompt

(FRS),(a ((mecha)) with sleek and menacing design:1.2), glowing eyes, full body, highly detailed, (heroic knight armor:0.8), (heroic parts:1.5) <lora:srdxl_v1f:0.8>

・レンジャーロボットスタイル Ranger Robot Style (RARS)

どこぞの特撮ヒーローで見かけるような巨大ロボットを出すスタイルです。箱形っぽい体系でかつ派手なカラーリングが特徴となっています。

もう少し箱っぽい要素ではなく、スーパーロボット要素を入れたい場合は「heroic parts」のプロジェクトを指定して強度を上げるといいでしょう。

The style is to produce a ranger-like robot that looks like a ranger you've seen somewhere before. When combined with the Super Robot style, it can produce robots with even more heroic designs.

サンプルプロンプト

sample prompt

(megazord), (SRS),a (((mecha))) with sleek and menacing design, glowing eyes, full body, highly detailed, (heroic parts), mechanical parts, robot joints, (city:1.2), <lora:srdxl_v1f:0.8>

・にじジャーニーロボットスタイル Niji Journey Robot Style (NJRS)

にじジャーニーで生成されたようなデザインのロボットを出すスタイルです。独特な造形とプロポーションが特徴となっております。

It reproduces the design and texture of the robot illustrations generated by Niji Journey. Enjoy the unique colours and designs.

サンプルプロンプト

sample prompt

(NJRS),a (((mecha))) with sleek and menacing design, glowing eyes, full body, highly detailed, (heroic parts), mechanical parts, robot joints, (city:1.2), <lora:srdxl_v1f:0.8>

items.name: Wolverine’s Claws (Weapon)
items.description:
This is the first time I am trying to train an object with which we should interact. I spent many days experimenting on this one. I couldn't find enough people discussing about how to properly train such object(it is especially a nightmare to deal with hands, so much harder than faces). Using my normal training settings, the model just cannot target what I want to train and result in bloody mess.

I have generated some right claws in txt2img, but I imagine this will be more useful in Inpainting. This Lora is far from perfect, in my testing, about one out of five times it will work properly(in Inpainting). I have retrained many times to get this model done (to the extent of at least useful in some cases). If it is useful to you, I would be more than happy to hear that.😊

If someone can suggest me some good tips or tutorial to train a specific body part or a small object that we can interact with, please leave me in the comment below. 🙏

This model is trained on Photon.

When you are using Inpainting, some tips may be useful.

  • Use ADetailer to make sure hands are ok

  • Sometimes it would be more natural if you mask out entire forearm, but it depends on what you want to change.

  • Leave some rooms for claws to grow.

  • Use slightly lower CFG Scale and DDIM sampler.(You can experiment with the settings)

  • You may want to put "muscle, arm hair" in the negative prompt.

  • Entirely white background is not good for this lora.

  • One hand at a time is highly suggested.

If you guys generated some good images, please share them below, they can help me improve the model. And if they are in high resolution, can even help me build a SDXL version.🙏

If you like this model, please consider leaving a like. Or you can buy me my next meal here. Thanks.❤️

Kofi: https://ko-fi.com/nextmealslider

items.name: Aries Spring (Astra Lost in Space / Kanata no Astra)
items.description:
Aries Spring (Astra Lost in Space / Kanata no Astra)

Please feel free to rate the model or share your creations with it. I'd be thrilled to see your works. If you find it useful, consider showing your appreciation by buying me a coffee.

  • Weight: between 0.8 to 1.0

  • Trigger Word: aries_spring

Additional Prompts:

  • Character: aries_spring, pink hair, short hair, hair ornament, heterochromia, green eyes, yellow eyes

  • Spacesuit: white bodysuit, pink gloves

  • Space Background: galaxy, spacecraft, starry sky

Cutoff Settings (Recommended):

  • Target tokens (character only): yellow,green,pink

  • Target tokens (character with white bodysuit): yellow,green,pink,white,pink

  • Weight: 0.5

Suggested Hires.fix configuration:

  • Upscaler (For Anime Models): R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B

  • Upscaler (For PhotoReal Models): R-ESRGAN 4x+

  • Hires steps: between 10 to 20

  • Denoising strength: between 0.15 to 0.35

This character is characterized by heterochromia, possessing one yellow eye and one green eye. I discovered that using a cutoff extension helps render them more consistently across various base models. An alternative approach to achieve stability is by increasing the weight of the prompts specifically related to the yellow eyes, green eyes, and heterochromia. This adjustment ensures a more accurate and balanced representation of the character's unique eye colors.

Your comments or suggestions are not only welcome but can significantly improve the quality of my models. They also motivate me to create more LoRA models. Feel free to connect with me on my Discord channel.

V1 was trained on the AnyLoRA base model with a dataset comprised of 33 images.

The compatibility of this LoRA model has been tested and work well with the following base models:

Anime models:

  • MeinaMix V11

  • DreamShaper V8

  • Perfect World V5

Photorealistic models:

  • AbsoluteReality V1

  • MoonMix V3 Reality

Cutoff Installation

Automatic1111 SD WebUI -> Extensions -> Install from URL

URL for extionsion's git repo: https://github.com/hnmr293/sd-webui-cutoff

Or, from Available tab search "cutoff".

Then click "Install" button.

For ComfyUI, please follow this guide.

All demonstration images showcased are randomly selected, not handpicked for optimal results.
